HEADWORD: Lanated
<hw>La"na*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <ety>[L. <ets>lanatus</ets>, fr. <ets>lana</ets> wool,
down.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Wooly; covered with fine long hair, or
hairlike filaments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>covered
with dense often matted or curly hairs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wooly, woolly.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lancashire boiler</ent>⟦br⟧
